105b. AccountsEditor layout wraps badly with Stocks % column
    Adding the Stocks % column caused account rows to wrap to two lines on
    normal-width screens. The bottom row (basis, stocks%, avail year, X button)
    loses its header association. Options:
    - Make the row horizontally scrollable in a container
    - Reduce column widths (abbreviate labels, use narrower inputs)
    - Move less-used fields (basis, stocks%, avail year) into an expandable
      detail row or popover per account
    - Use a responsive grid that reflows better than flex-wrap



106. Estimate growth/income from investment balance
    Use stock_pct and account balances to estimate expected dividend/interest income
    and expected capital appreciation separately. This would allow:
    - Showing estimated annual investment income (dividends + interest) on a per-account
      or portfolio basis
    - Pre-filling growth rate suggestions based on actual allocation rather than just
      the blended OFX import estimate
    - Displaying expected tax drag more concretely (e.g. "~$2,300/yr in brokerage tax drag")
    - Potentially modeling reinvested vs distributed income differently

